                    <td class="views-field views-field-field-opening-positions" > 1 </td>
                    <td class="views-field views-field-body" ><p>Ref. #: 5619.008<br />
                        JOB LOCATION: Twinsburg, Ohio<br />
                        JOB DUTIES: ):  Coordinating a team of up to 20 software developers and systems analysts on assigned client IT projects. Work with clients to develop project plans to be approved by decision makers. Submit and Track project milestones and deliverables in accordance with Vertex's best practices. Work with key parties to resolve problems that arise and ensure successful project completion. Engage in requirements gathering, analysis, and specification development for Enterprise Applications, ETL, Infrastructure upgrade and system/network security. Act as a scrum master and mentor, conduct scrum calls, sprint planning, product backlog refinement sessions, maintain product backlog, create burn down chart etc. Regularly update Vertex and client management regarding project status. Ensure client satisfaction with developed systems. Travel and/or relocation to various unanticipated locations throughout the U.S. required. Utilize the following tools and technologies: Oracle 11g, HP Quality Center, Oracle Retail Suite, MS Access, MS SharePoint, SQL.</p>
                      <p>SPECIAL SKILLS:<br />
                        Position requires a Master's Degree in Computer Information Systems, Engineering Management, Computer Science or Engineering and one year experience. One (1) year experience must have included: (1) Oracle 11g, (2) HP Quality Center, (3) Oracle Retail Suite, (4) MS Access, (5) MS SharePoint, and (6) SQL. Travel and/or Relocation to various unanticipated locations throughout the US required.</p>
                      <p>TO APPLY:<br />
                        Please send resume and cover letter referencing Ref. # 5619.008 to Vertex Computer Systems, Inc., ATTN: Sharda Iyer, 2245 Enterprise Parkway East, Twinsburg, Ohio 44087.</p></td>
                  </tr>
