                        JOB LOCATION: Twinsburg, Ohio<br />
                        JOB DUTIES:<br />
                        Responsible for designing new equipment and systems taking into account cost, availability of materials, strength and maintenance requirements.  Maintaining a database of all the machine designs using Teamcenter (TCUA)-PLM Suite.  Actively involved in the concept, design and manufacturing stages of a product life cycle.  Coordinating multi-discipline design teams from concept through project completion by coordinating with Vendors, fabricators and suppliers.  Research and analyze customer proposals, specifications, manuals and other data to evaluate the feasibility, cost and maintenance requirements of designs.  Read and interpret blueprints, technical drawings, schematics, and computer-generated reports.  Provide technical input to spares enquiries and orders to ensure that the correct components to the latest design are used and to ensure quality control.  Develop product design solutions compliant with industry and regulatory standards (UL/ANSI).  Coordination of inter disciplinary activities, project expedition, project scheduling, progress reporting, &amp; controlling.  Interact with cross-functional teams (engineering, manufacturing, sourcing, and finance and product management, vendors) to define requirements, validate designs, implement products into production and support on-going operations.  Travel and/or relocation to various unanticipated locations throughout the U.S. required.  Work with the following tools and technologies: Pro E, Solid Edge, Solid Works, Teamcenter PLM Software, Six Sigma. </p>
                      <p>SPECIAL SKILLS:<br />
                        Position requires a Master's Degree in Aerospace Engineering or Mechanical Engineering and twelve (12) months experience. One (1) year experience must have included: Pro E, Solid Edge, Solid Works, Teamcenter PLM Software, Six Sigma. Travel and/or relocation to various unanticipated locations throughout the U.S. required.</p>
